Canonical style (neutral, professional, UMRS-aligned)

At the top of the file or above the relevant block:

// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
//
// Portions of this file were contributed by:
//   Jane Doe <jane@example.org>
//   - Initial x86_64 CPUID parsing logic
//   - IFUNC detection improvements
//
// See CONTRIBUTORS.md for full contributor acknowledgments.

Or for a localized contribution:

// NOTE:
//   The virtualization detection heuristics below were contributed by
//   Alex Smith <alex@security.example>
//   (commit 3f7a2c9, 2026-02-14)
//
//   Rationale: Detect masked CPU features in KVM/Parallels guests.

Key rules (so it doesn’t get messy):
	•	Do not add an attribution comment for tiny typo fixes
	•	Do not add “thank you!” style fluff in code
	•	Do not embed legal terms in these comments
	•	Always:
	•	Name
	•	Email or handle
	•	What they contributed
	•	(Optional but excellent) commit hash
